Class Ship

  • java.lang.Object
    • main.Ship
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IShip

    public class Ship
extends java.lang.Object
implements IShip
    A class of ships that have a position, velocity, radius, and direction. Ships can move, apply thrust and turn. The class also provides functionality for collision detection.
    Version:
    0.1
    Author:
    Jasper
    Invariants:
  • A ship's speed limit can never exceed the speed of light (c=300000 km/s).
        getSpeedLimit =< 300000
  • A ship's speed can never exceed it's speed limit.
        getVelocity =< getSpeedLimit

      • move

        public void move(double dt)
        Moves the ship for a duration dt according to its current state. The ship will be moved according to its current position and its current velocity during the specified duration dt. The specified duration dt can never be less than zero.
        Parameters:
        dt - Specifies the duration of the move command.
        Postcondition:
        The new xPos (yPos) is equal to the old xPos (yPos) changed by the xVelocity (yVelocity) multiplied by the given duration.
            new this.getX() = this.getX() + getXVelocity*dt
            new this.getY() = this.getY() + getYVelocity*dt
        Throws:
        - [CAN]

      • thrust

        public void thrust(double da)
        Changes the velocity of the ship by an amount da. This method changes the velocity of the ship according to its current velocity and the direction it's facing. The change in total velocity will be equal to the specified amount da.
        Parameters:
        da - The total velocity to be added to the ship's current velocity.
        Postconditions:
      • If the given amount of change in velocity is equal to or less than zero, no change to the ship's velocity is made.
            if(da =< 0) then
                  new getXVelocity = getXVelocity
                  new getYVelocity = getYVelocity
      • The new velocity vector is equal to the old velocity vector changed by the given amount da in the ship's current direction.
            new getXVelocity = getXVelocity + da*cos(angle)
            new getYVelocity = getYVelocity + da*sin(angle)
      • If the new total velocity would exceed the ship's upper speed limit, the new total velocity is equal to the speed of light.
